The paper discusses a probabilistic regression model that incorporates Gaussian processes (GPs) into sum-product networks (SPNs) for efficient and exact posterior inference. This work involves machine learning and probabilistic modeling, which are typically covered in the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on real-world data, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the model's ability to account for non-stationarities in time series, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
